The American soldiers have a new "smart weapon"
The US military is deploying a new "smart" weapon in Afghanistan, known for now only by the code name XM-25.
The generals hope the new rifle will influence the local conflict with the Taliban and "change the game's progress" toward their victory.
The new weapons are like a small pistol with an extremely precise aiming.
Their bullets are fired with a laser with a precision of several meters.
The special 25mm caliber ammunition created for this rifle and the high load of explosives it contains causes it to actually function like a small grenade.
The projectiles can be programmed to explode not only when they hit the target, but at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
They can be used against enemies hiding behind an obstacle, a wall or a trench.
Of course, normal protection cannot be used and, when it throws its killer rain of metallic flakes, it can prove essential in battle.
According to Richard Audette, who spoke about the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon to use "smart" technology.
