"He composed it with sounds from the Middle East and numerous scales and rhythms from North Africa", Dorman said in a telephone interview.
Director Pierre Boulez, 85, was nominated in the category of orchestral performance, for conducting the Chicago Symphony Orchestra during a recording of Stravinsky's works.
