They could receive up to a total of 100 millimeters of rain.
Since these precipitation increases the snow melting that has already accumulated in certain areas, several rivers are feared to overflow.
On Wednesday night, the Quebec Civil Security unit issued alerts for the Ouareau and Achigan rivers in Lanaudière.
The northern rivers in Saint-Jérôme, Laurentides and Chêne, Lotbinière, have already caused flooding in the past and are under surveillance.
In the Lanaudière region, heavy rainfall has caused some lakes to overflow in Sainte-Julienne, Sainte-Marcelline-de-Kildare and Rawdon.
In Saint-Calixte, heavy rains have dragged a temporary bridge.
As a precaution, ten residences have been evacuated.
In Outaouais, the overflow of certain lakes has led to the closure of several roads, in particular in the municipality of Mansfield-et-Pontefract.
The Civil Security Unit remains on alert and closely monitors the situation, according to Annik Bouchard, security adviser.
